
Overview of noun toilet

The noun toilet has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) toilet, lavatory, lav, can, john, privy, bathroom -- (a room or building equipped with one or more toilets)
2. (2) toilet, can, commode, crapper, pot, potty, stool, throne -- (a plumbing fixture for defecation and urination)
3. gutter, sewer, toilet -- (misfortune resulting in lost effort or money; "his career was in the gutter"; "all that work went down the sewer"; "pensions are in the toilet")
4. toilet, toilette -- (the act of dressing and preparing yourself; "he made his morning toilet and went to breakfast")
